It's almost vacation time!  Me and Carol are doing Disney again, and then I'm spending a few days in Nanaimo with Carol.  I'm going on a shopping spree @ Value Village (& stores in the mall) to get skinny clothes (and inbetween ones, too).  I'm also going to get my hair done again (cut, dyed, permed).  I can't WAIT!!!  I leave here on the 20th, go to cali on the 21, in disney from 22-27 minus one day for knotts berry farm, go to nanaimo on the 28 and finally back home on the 6.

Also, I changed my LJ layout, and am working on a custom mood theme too :D  What do you think?

So, Dwaine doesn't have brain cancer, but they're pretty sure his lung cancer is back :( The "lesions" in his brain were just from his bleed years ago in his accident; apparantly the dr. didn't COMPARE!!! So the past few days I've been purusing craft blogs online and have come with OODLES of cool stuff to do :)  The only thing, now, is to find the time to do it.

Not that I don't have the time, but I just tend to waste my time ;)

Well...I'm kind of off of audit.  I work from 5-1:30 (normally it'd be 2:30-11 or 3-11:30) to start the audit for Jacques and be there if he needs any help initially.  This week I'm pretty much 'coddling' him (counting all the tills, sorting all the front desk, counting all the meal vouchers, doing his gift shop & banquets) so all he has to focus on, really, is the restaurant tab (which is the most troublesome b/c it always has mistakes.

After about a month of this, I'll be doing James' audit shifts (so i'll have 3 days desk, 2 days audit) to give James a treat after working so hard for that first week 1/2 that Jacques was out.  And after that?  Probably 5 days audit for a month to month-and-a-half b/c Jacques is probably going to have to go have his arteries cleaned (the rototiller, as he calls it lol!)

And: they gypped me out of my pay!!!!  On audit I get paid $14 an hour, on desk it's $12.  My first week of audit, they gave me $12.  It works out to a difference of only $77 but that's $77!!!

Didn't do so well at the market last week, but the weather sucked to boot.  So!  This week should be awesome, by rights.

Well...what an unexpected turn of events.  Due to medical reasons, our current full-time auditor is unable to work...leaving our old full-time, now part-time, doing all the audits -- except he has another job within the hotel AND one outside of it too!!  So....long story short: I am the new full-time auditor (for a few weeks, at least).

I'm still sick, and it seems I will be for another day or two :(.  This is sooo not fun (especially since I have to go into work, to boot.  Whoohoo...go to work with an upset stummy)

I just took a nap, for an hour...I woke up just before my alarm went off, and felt like I had slept for all night!!  

It finally seems like spring out, again.  It's warming up, an all the snow is melting.  But, I'm not getting my hopes up -- it's supposed to snow the next 2 days, and any ideas of spring will be long gone again.

Late a few nights ago I bid on (and won) a beautiful bracelet on ebay. See it here. And now I'm on so late because I had to go pay for it (b/c I was sick yesterday and couldn't)...and now I'm going to bed, to get up really early tomorrow. (Promise a better post tomorrow!!)

Yesterday I thought it was that Shamrock Shake that didn't agree with me, but I'm still sick today :(  And I have to go to a staff meeting.  At least I'm starting to feel better (thirsty, though, but all I have is water.  I hate drinking water when i'm sick)

After the staff meeting I might see if my mom can take me to get apple juice.

How's your middle of the week?
